  "title": "Triggering a re-render by changing vue state resets hierarchical menu",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen using a hierarchical menu, a vue triggered re-render resets it and performs a new search. This only seems to happen for hierarchical menus, though I have only compared against refinement lists at the moment. Refinement lists also get added to the browser url after triggering the re-render.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a Vue Instantsearch component with a hierarchical menu\n3. Add any component that changes the state and triggers a vue rerender\n4. Select something in the hierarchical menu\n5. Trigger a rerender, e.g. by clicking a button that changes the state\n6. The hierarchical menu gets reset, without mapping the router state again### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/zealous-meadow-97dkdc\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nThe current ui state should be retained, regardless of a vue re-render.\n\n### Package version\n\nvue-instantsearch@4.19.13 vue@2.7.16 typesense-instantsearch-adapter@2.8.0 (I am using typesense here, but that should not make a difference)\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
